<br>
Also, hybrid classes should wait or completely avoid casting spells while in melee on big mobs.  This may include HT.  From what I have seen the biggest problem on the large mobs is people taking aggro (either from being too close or casting) when they aren't supposed to and dying fast.  We don't have a 60 tank, so don't fight like we do =P.  It's hard enough as it is to have tanks keep aggro, as we have no spells or discs or abilities to do so.<br>
<br>
Casters seem to cast too early in itself, and anyway most big mobs just have too high MR for most things.<br>
<br>
This guild is great with smaller mobs, except for surrounding them and getting on one mob in a crowded area with mezzed mobs and multiple mobs of the same name.  I think the hole may be a good practice raid area for all as it is not quite as hard as some other zones, doesn't require a great deal of people, and the mobs still have the big zone reactions (easy aggro, gate, etc.)<br>
<br>
To be honest, this guild would do great in PoG if we had enough going.  Lots of mobs to be pushed and nice drops etc. <p><TABLE ALIGN=CENTER>
